# Walkthrough: Groww RAG Chatbot Final Implementation

We have built a production-ready RAG chatbot architecture for Groww, featuring automated data updates, strict source attribution, and a premium UI.

## Final Project Structure
```text
RAG Chatbot/
├── phase_1_ingestion/
│   └── ingested_data.json      # Raw scraped data
├── phase_2_processing_indexing/
│   ├── processor.py            # Data transformation
│   ├── processed_data.json     # Cleaned chunks
│   └── vector_index.json       # Searchable index
├── phase_3_retrieval_generation/
│   ├── chatbot.py              # LLM + Retrieval logic
│   └── prompt_template.py      # AI guardrails
├── phase_4_frontend_backend/
│   ├── server.py               # Zero-dependency backend
│   └── static/                 # Premium UI assets
└── phase_5_scheduler_pipeline/
    ├── scheduler.py            # The Orchestrator
    ├── health_check.py         # System Validator
    ├── data_hash.txt           # Change detection
    └── scheduler.log           # Step-by-step logs
```

## Refined Phase 5: The Scheduler Pipeline
The final phase ensures the bot is always current:
1. **Automation**: [scheduler.py](file:///Users/vidushipatel/Documents/Code/RAG%20Chatbot/phase_5_scheduler_pipeline/scheduler.py) runs every 24 hours (configurable).
2. **Intelligence**: It uses MD5 hashing to detect actual data changes before expensive re-processing.
3. **Validation**: Post-update, it runs a suite of tests in [health_check.py](file:///Users/vidushipatel/Documents/Code/RAG%20Chatbot/phase_5_scheduler_pipeline/health_check.py) to guarantee source link accuracy and retrieval performance.
4. **UI Integration**: The frontend now displays the exact time of the last successful update.

